# Rust Code Patterns for u-forge.ai

Design decisions and hard-won rules. Source files are thoroughly commented — read
them for the mechanics. This file exists so the *why* can be intuited without
re-reading the code.

---

## Error Handling

- **`anyhow::Result`** for internal fallible operations throughout the codebase.
  `.context()` wraps lower-level errors; `anyhow!(...)` constructs formatted
  errors.
- **`thiserror::Error`** for typed error enums at system boundaries (e.g. HTTP
  handler responses, where consumers need to discriminate variants). `thiserror`
  generates `Display`/`From`/`std::error::Error` — do not hand-write them.

Rule of thumb: if a caller will pattern-match on the error, use `thiserror`;
otherwise `anyhow` with `.context()`.

