## FTS5 invariants

`chunks_fts` is a virtual table mirroring `chunks(content)`. Kept in sync by
three DML triggers defined in `SQL_SCHEMA` (storage.rs).

**Never manually `INSERT` into `chunks_fts`.** Always go through `upsert_chunk`.
The triggers handle insert/update/delete — bypassing them leaves the FTS index
out of sync with the chunks table, producing phantom or missing search hits.

Query syntax supported by the `search_chunks_fts` wrapper: phrase (`"hari
seldon"`), prefix (`found*`), boolean (`empire AND foundation`), column filters.
Illegal characters must be stripped first — see `src/search/sanitize.rs`
(`fts5_sanitize`). The original query is still passed verbatim to `embed()` and
`rerank()`, where punctuation is meaningful.

---

## ANN vector search (sqlite-vec)

Two vector tables, both cosine distance:
- `chunks_vec` — 768-dim (standard embeddings, any compatible model)
- `chunks_vec_hq` — 4096-dim (only when an HQ model like
  `Qwen3-Embedding-8B-GGUF` is configured)

The two vector spaces are **fixed and incompatible**. Never mix models from
incompatible dimension spaces in the same index.

Same sync contract as FTS: DML triggers keep both indexes consistent; chunk
deletion cascades to vectors. **Never manually manage `chunks_vec` /
`chunks_vec_hq`** — always go through `upsert_chunk_embedding` /
`upsert_chunk_embedding_hq`.

A chunk must be explicitly indexed before it becomes searchable via ANN. The
incremental embedding workflow (`do_embed_all`) checks `GraphStats.embedded_count`
and skips work when the index is already populated — startup builds embeddings
once; subsequent starts are fast.

