## Performance instrumentation

Use structured `tracing` fields (`key = value`), not format strings. Logs are
machine-parseable and grep-friendly by field.

```rust
tracing::debug!(
    operation = "fts_search",
    query = %query,
    results = result.len(),
    duration_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis(),
    "Search completed"
);
```

`%` calls `Display`, `?` calls `Debug`.

For async entry points, prefer `#[instrument(skip_all, fields(...))]` over bare
`#[instrument]` — it avoids auto-capturing large structs and lets you record
fields manually via `Span::current().record(...)` after the fact (e.g. recording
`pending_jobs` after calling `stats()`). See `dispatch.rs::embed` for the pattern.

For spawned tasks that outlive the calling frame, attach a span with
`.instrument(tracing::info_span!("task_name"))` on the future before detaching.
See `app_view/mod.rs::run_embedding_plan` and `do_init_lemonade`.

